{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.3",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 3 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:1",
      "text": "My son, don’t forget my teaching, but let your heart keep my commandments,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:2",
      "text": "for they will add to you length of days, years of life, and peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:3",
      "text": "Don’t let kindness and truth forsake you. Bind them around your neck. Write them on the tablet of your heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:4",
      "text": "So you will find favor, and good understanding in the sight of God and man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:5",
      "text": "Trust in Yahweh with all your heart, and don’t lean on your own understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:6",
      "text": "In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make your paths straight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:7",
      "text": "Don’t be wise in your own eyes. Fear Yahweh, and depart from evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:8",
      "text": "It will be health to your body, and nourishment to your bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:9",
      "text": "Honor Yahweh with your substance, with the first fruits of all your increase;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:10",
      "text": "so your barns will be filled with plenty, and your vats will overflow with new wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:11",
      "text": "My son, don’t despise Yahweh’s discipline, neither be weary of his correction;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:12",
      "text": "for whom Yahweh loves, he corrects, even as a father reproves the son in whom he delights.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:13",
      "text": "Happy is the man who finds wisdom, the man who gets understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:14",
      "text": "For her good profit is better than getting silver, and her return is better than fine gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:15",
      "text": "She is more precious than rubies. None of the things you can desire are to be compared to her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:16",
      "text": "Length of days is in her right hand. In her left hand are riches and honor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:17",
      "text": "Her ways are ways of pleasantness. All her paths are peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:18",
      "text": "She is a tree of life to those who lay hold of her. Happy is everyone who retains her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:19",
      "text": "By wisdom Yahweh founded the earth. By understanding, he established the heavens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:20",
      "text": "By his knowledge, the depths were broken up, and the skies drop down the dew.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:21",
      "text": "My son, let them not depart from your eyes. Keep sound wisdom and discretion,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:22",
      "text": "so they will be life to your soul, and grace for your neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:23",
      "text": "Then you shall walk in your way securely. Your foot won’t stumble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:24",
      "text": "When you lie down, you will not be afraid. Yes, you will lie down, and your sleep will be sweet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:25",
      "text": "Don’t be afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it comes;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:26",
      "text": "for Yahweh will be your confidence, and will keep your foot from being taken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:27",
      "text": "Don’t withhold good from those to whom it is due, when it is in the power of your hand to do it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:28",
      "text": "Don’t say to your neighbor, “Go, and come again; tomorrow I will give it to you,” when you have it by you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:29",
      "text": "Don’t devise evil against your neighbor, since he dwells securely by you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:30",
      "text": "Don’t strive with a man without cause, if he has done you no harm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:31",
      "text": "Don’t envy the man of violence. Choose none of his ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:32",
      "text": "For the perverse is an abomination to Yahweh, but his friendship is with the upright.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:33",
      "text": "Yahweh’s curse is in the house of the wicked, but he blesses the habitation of the righteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:34",
      "text": "Surely he mocks the mockers, but he gives grace to the humble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.3.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:35",
      "text": "The wise will inherit glory, but shame will be the promotion of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
